Below is a complete, self-contained mini-site that does everything you asked for:
â€¢  Landing page with a big â€œBROWSE DEALSâ€ button
â€¢  Two scrollable lists:
â€“ â€œOn Sale Nowâ€ (auto-fetched from the cheapshark API)
â€“ â€œComing Soonâ€ (static demo data so we donâ€™t need a second API key)
â€¢  Live search box that filters both lists instantly
â€¢  One-click â€œNotify meâ€ on any upcoming game
â€¢  The browser will ask permission for push notifications; when the user grants it we store the subscription server-side (demo server included) so you can send real updates later
Copy everything into a folder, open index.html, and youâ€™re live.
If you want it on Google, push the folder to GitHub Pages and add the site in Search Console â€“ itâ€™s already crawler-friendly.
----
FILE: index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8"/>
  <title>GameDeals HQ â€“ new sales & upcoming releases</title>
  <meta name="description" content="See the newest video-game deals and upcoming releases in one place. Set release alerts."/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"/>
  <link rel="manifest" href="manifest.json"/>
  <script defer src="app.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>ğŸ® GameDeals HQ</h1>
    <input id="search" type="search" placeholder="Search any gameâ€¦" autocomplete="off"/>
  </header>

  <section id="hero">
    <h2>Fresh deals & upcoming titles</h2>
    <p>Never miss a price drop or a launch day again.</p>
    <button id="browseBtn" class="cta">BROWSE DEALS</button>
  </section>

  <main id="content" hidden>
    <div class="col">
      <h3>ğŸ”¥ On Sale Now</h3>
      <ul id="dealsList" class="gameList"></ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <h3>ğŸ“… Coming Soon</h3>
      <ul id="upcomingList" class="gameList"></ul>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>Built for demo purposes â€“ swap in your own APIs any time.</footer>

  <!-- Push-notification toast -->
  <div id="toast"></div>
</body>
</html>

